  "original_title": "\u0da0\u0dd3\u0db1\u0dba\u0dda \u0da7\u0dd2\u0dba\u0dcf\u0db1\u0dca\u0dc2\u0ddd-3 \u0db7\u0dcf\u0dab\u0dca\u0da9 \u0db4\u0dca\u200d\u0dbb\u0dc0\u0dcf\u0dc4\u0db1 \u0dba\u0dcf\u0db1\u0dba \u0dba\u0dc5\u0dd2 \u0db4\u0dd8\u0dae\u0dd2\u0dc0\u0dd2\u0dba\u0da7",
  "text_idx": {
    "en": {
      "title": "China's Tianshou-3 cargo plane returns to Earth",
      "author": "unknown",
      "body_lines": [
        "Tianshou-3, a cargo spacecraft carrying supplies to China's space station, made a controlled re-entry into Earth's atmosphere at 11:31 a.m. (Beijing time) on Wednesday, the China Manned Space Agency said.",
        "The LongMarch-7 Y4 rocket carrying Tianzhou-3 had lifted off from the Wenchang Spacecraft Launch Site in South China's Hainan Province at 3:10 PM on September 20, 2021.",
        "It was carrying about 6 tonnes of cargo, including food and spacesuits, to the space station under construction from China. Six and a half hours later, the cargo spacecraft docked with its main module Tianhe at 10:08 p.m.",
        "The core module of the Tianzhou-3 space station separated from Tianshe on July 17, 2022 after completing all assigned assembly tasks.",
        "It is the third mission of China's Tianzhou-class unmanned cargo spacecraft, and the second resupply mission to the space station after Tianzhou-2."
      ],
